testcaseName: Dose #1 Unspecified Covid 19 vaccine, Dose #2 given as Janssen

administeredDoses.evaluationReason: Not a preferable or allowable vaccine

doses.evaluationReason: Not a preferable or allowable vaccine

generalDescription: This test case describes when a patient has been administered the first dose of the Covid-19 vaccine as Unspecified, and a second dose, given at 4 weeks later,  as Janssen, that the Janssen dose is valid. Another dose should be forecast.
reasonForChange: v4.13 - Updated test case to include ACIP recommendation where if the first dose of a Covid-19 vaccine is followed with a second dose of Janssen, that another dose should be forecast.
